<P>
Waco sect's new church won't be ready by April 19 anniversary
</P>
<P>
   WACO, Texas (AP) -- Due to lagging donations and lack of
volunteer labor, the remaining Branch Davidians won't have a new
church ready for the seventh anniversary of their fiery standoff
with federal agents.
</P>
<P>
   The group plans to worship at the site of the tragedy April 19,
but builders said the new church will probably lack seating,
flooring and plumbing.
</P>
<P>
   Davidians who survived the 51-day standoff say the project began
when libertarian radio talk show host Alex Jones and an aide asked
what they could do to help David Koresh's remaining disciples
restore what they lost in 1993.
</P>
<P>
   Some $83,000 has been donated.
</P>
