<P>
Indiana diocese to forgive church debts
</P>
<P>
   GARY, Ind. (AP) -- Citing a strong economy and the principle of
stewardship, the Roman Catholic diocese of Gary said it will reduce
or forgive debts of $2.8 million for eight parishes and
institutions.
</P>
<P>
   Diocesan spokesman Brian Olszewski said investment earnings made
the plan possible. ''We're a forgiving church. We practice what we
preach,'' he said. ''Through the country, I think more and more
dioceses will be doing this.''
</P>
<P>
   A typical beneficiary is St. Mary of the Lake parish. ''To keep
the school running, for a while we had to pump money in. The parish
could no longer do it,'' said the Rev. Tom Mischler. ''It truly is
a weight lifted off us. We can begin to think about creating
programs. People are attracted to a parish when they see action.''
</P>
