<HEADLINE> Faith Hill Dominates TNN Nominations  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Give Faith Hill some room to
''Breathe.''
</P>
<P>
   The country music diva and her hit dominated the nominations for
the TNN Awards with eight. Hill was nominated for best entertainer
and female vocalist, and ''Breathe'' is up for best single, video,
song and album.
</P>
<P>
   Not far behind Hill was husband Tim McGraw, who had five
nominations. George Strait, with six nominations, McGraw and Hill
were joined in the top category of best entertainer by Alan Jackson
and Shania Twain.
</P>
<P>
   Hill and McGraw were also nominated for best vocal collaboration
for their duet ''Let's Make Love.''
</P>
<P>
   The nominations came from fans and music industry workers. Fans
will vote for the winners through telephone numbers announced on
TNN, ballots in Country Weekly magazine and two Internet sites
(http://country.com and http://www.countryweekly.com).
</P>
<P>
   Best male vocalist nominees were Jackson, McGraw, Strait, Kenny
Chesney and Vince Gill. In addition to Hill, Martina McBride, Reba
McEntire, Jo Dee Messina and Twain were nominated for best female
vocalist.
</P>
<P>
   The TNN Awards, set for June 15 in Nashville, are the second of
three major annual country music awards shows. The show will cap
the annual week-long International Country Music Fan Fair festival.
</P>
