<HEADLINE> Smits Graces School Opening  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Jimmy Smits shouted ''Viva la educacion'' as he
snipped a ribbon at the ceremonial opening of a charter school, but
some students weren't sure just who he was.
</P>
<P>
   Though many know Smits as the star of prime-time serials ''NYPD
Blue'' and ''LA Law,'' some middle-schoolers were puzzled about the
identity of the guy with the goatee, hoop earring and stretch limo.
</P>
<P>
   ''Wasn't he in 'The Godfather?''' one youngster whispered.
</P>
<P>
   Smits, in South Florida to promote his upcoming film, ''Price of
Glory,'' about a Latin boxing family, offered a pep talk Wednesday
at the ASPIRA Youth Leadership Charter School in North Miami.
</P>
<P>
   Founded by a Puerto Rican woman, ASPIRA encourages minority
students. Smits won a scholarship from the organization when he was
a struggling college student in Brooklyn in the 1970s.
</P>
<P>
   Proceeds from the film's Miami premiere went to ASPIRA, among
other charities.
</P>
