<HEADLINE> Gov.: JonBenet Parents Still Hiding  </HEADLINE>
By STEVEN K. PAULSON, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER (AP) -- Gov. Bill Owens said Thursday that John and Patsy
Ramsey are trying to manipulate the public into believing they are
victims even though the couple continues to hide behind their
lawyers.
</P>
<P>
   The Ramseys are promoting their new book in which they theorize
that an intruder killed their daughter JonBenet.
</P>
<P>
   Owens stopped short of calling the Ramseys suspects in
JonBenet's slaying but contended they are trying to ''orchestrate a
feeling across the country that they are the victims in the case.''
</P>
<P>
   ''What bothers me is they wouldn't talk when it mattered and now
you're not going to be able to pick up a publication or turn on the
TV without seeing them talking,'' he said. ''I just find it strange
behavior for them to try to become the victims.''
</P>
<P>
   The governor made the comments after he read excerpts from the
Ramseys' book, ''The Death of Innocence,'' which is scheduled to go
on sale Friday.
</P>
<P>
   In interviews with ABC's ''20/20,'' set to air Friday, and NBC's
''Today'' show, set to air next week, the Ramseys said they believe
an intruder, perhaps a male pedophile, waited in their home for
hours before he strangled and beat JonBenet in a soured kidnapping
attempt.
</P>
<P>
   Her body was found in the basement of the family's Boulder home
on Dec. 26, 1996.
</P>
<P>
   Boulder authorities have said the Ramseys remain under an
umbrella of suspicion. A Boulder County grand jury examined
evidence for 13 months before disbanding. No charges were filed and
the Ramseys adamantly maintain their innocence.
</P>
<P>
   In October, Owens urged the Ramseys to return to Colorado from
their Atlanta area home and cooperate with authorities to try to
solve the crime.
</P>
<P>
   Owens said Thursday the Ramseys ''hid behind lawyers and PR
firms from Day One and they're still hiding.''
</P>
<P>
   In their book, the Ramseys accused Owens of making his remarks
for political gain.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
