<HEADLINE> Barnes &AMP; Noble's Earnings Rise  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Barnes &AMP; Noble Inc.'s rose more than 9 percent
on Thursday after the giant bookseller reported its sales and
profits climbed in the fourth quarter, fueled by strong results at
its large bookstores.
</P>
<P>
   The New York-based company said Thursday that it earned $103.5
million, or $1.48 cents a share, in the quarter ended Jan. 29,
2000, compared with $106 million, or $1.47 a share a year ago.
</P>
<P>
   Profits from operations -- which include earnings from the
company's bookstores and Babbage's Etc. software chain as well as a
loss at the Barnes &AMP; Noble.com Internet unit but exclude other
investment gains -- were $1.27 a share, compared with 90 cents a
year ago.
</P>
<P>
   The results topped Wall Street analysts' estimates of $1.25 a
share. The company's stock rose $2.12{ to $20.06\ in trading on the
New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
   Despite the increased popularity of online bookstores, Barnes &AMP;
Noble managed to have a very strong 1999, and the company expects
its solid performance to extend into 2000.
</P>
<P>
   Sales for the quarter were $1.34 billion, up from $1.03 billion
a year ago. For the year, sales were $3.49 billion, up from $3.01
billion in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   The results were especially strong at Barnes &AMP; Noble's
superstores, with sales rising 12.2 percent for the year. Sales at
the large-format stores open at least a year, an industry gauge of
performance, rose 6.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The only weak spot came at its B. Dalton bookstores, where sales
fell 9.1 percent from a year ago. The company closed 89 stores
during the year at the chain, which is mostly found in malls.
</P>
<P>
   Sales at B. Dalton stores open at least a year were up 0.1
percent in 1999.
</P>
<P>
   In its Babbage's chain, sales rose 18.9 percent, and same-store
sales were up 12.5 percent. Barnes &AMP; Noble said the acquisition of
Babbage's, which it purchased in October, added 10 cents a share to
its earnings.
</P>
<P>
   For the year, Barnes &AMP; Noble earned $124.5 million, or $1.75 a
share, compared with $92.38 million, or $1.29 a share a year ago.
</P>
<P>
   At the end of its fiscal year in January, the company operated
542 superstores, 400 B. Dalton stores and 526 Babbage's stores.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-03-16-00 1715 </TRAILER>
