<HEADLINE> Suspected Robber Killed by Fla. Cops  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) -- Police shot and killed a man
suspected of being a bank robber after a two-hour standoff Thursday
in an office building hallway as 50 workers hid behind locked
doors.
</P>
<P>
   The armed man, William McCarthy Pettit, was suspected of holding
up a NationsBank branch down the street. He fled into Cypress Creek
Business Park and was shot by police when he made a sudden and
suspicious move, police spokesman Mike Reed said.
</P>
<P>
   ''He was shot by SWAT team members in the hallway,'' Reed said.
''I don't know if he was threatening them.''
</P>
<P>
   No one else was injured.
</P>
<P>
   Pettit, 46, died at a hospital, Reed said.
</P>
<P>
   Pettit allegedly walked into the bank with a pistol, took an
undisclosed amount of cash and fled. As police looked for him on
foot and from a helicopter, someone from the nearby office building
called 911 to report a suspicious person.
</P>
<P>
   Pettit ran into a bathroom on the second floor. Police said they
didn't evacuate the building because the workers were safer inside.
</P>
