<HEADLINE> Report: Militants Kill 11 in Algeria  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALGIERS, Algeria (AP) -- Militants shot or stabbed to death seven
children and four adults in western Algeria at the end of a Muslim
holiday, the official APS news agency said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The attack Wednesday evening in Hatatba, 30 miles west of the
capital Algiers, came at the end of Aid El Kebir, a three-day
religious holiday that occurs 40 days after the end of Ramadan. It
commemorates the biblical story where Abraham is asked by God to
kill his son.
</P>
<P>
   President Abdelaziz Bouteflika has tried to restore peace to the
north African nation, but some Islamic militants have rejected a
government-backed partial amnesty.
</P>
<P>
   A militant insurgency began in 1992 after the army canceled
legislative elections that an Islamic party was poised to win. More
than 100,000 people have since died in the violence.
</P>
<P>
   Religious holidays are often marked by a rise in violence.
Scores of people were killed in massacres during the holy month of
Ramadan last December.
</P>
</TEXT>
