<HEADLINE> Ducruet Says He Was Set Up  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NICE, France (AP) -- Daniel Ducruet, divorced by Monaco's
Princess Stephanie after the publication of photographs showing him
frolicking with a Belgian stripper, told a French court Thursday
that he had been set up.
</P>
<P>
   Ducruet said he might even have been drugged when photographs
showing him in a poolside romp with Fili Houteman, the
then-reigning Miss Nude Belgium, were taken in 1996.
</P>
<P>
   Houteman told the court that she was not aware of any plot and
had simply ''succumbed'' to Ducruet's advances.
</P>
<P>
   Ducruet charged that he was the victim of a sting operation and
prosecutors are seeking a one-year suspended prison sentence for
Houteman and six months in prison for photographer Stephane de
Lisiecki and alleged accomplice Yves Hoogewis, as well as $22,000.
</P>
<P>
   De Lisiecki said he had rented a villa in the southeastern
France and reserved plane tickets for Houteman. But he said he only
hoped for a photograph of a kiss.
</P>
<P>
   The court was due to give its verdict Apr. 27.
</P>
<P>
   Stephanie was granted a speedy divorce in October 1996, weeks
after two Italian magazines printed 40 pages of explicit photos
between Ducruet and Houteman.
</P>
<P>
   The scandal rocked Monaco. Stephanie and Ducruet had two
children.
</P>
</TEXT>
