<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Leeds, Arsenal Win in UEFA Cup  </HEADLINE>
By ROBERT MILLWARD, AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   Thierry Henry and Fredrik Ljungberg scored as Arsenal beat
Werder Bremen 2-0 Thursday night in the first leg UEFA Cup
quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
   At Highbury in London, Henry scored in the 21st minute off a
long pass from Patrick Vieira that beat an offside trap, and
Ljungberg scored with 15 minutes left after collecting a shot that
Nwanko Kanu mis-hit.
</P>
<P>
   At Eiland Road, Leeds defeated Slavia Prague 3-0 as Lee Bowyer
scored one goal and set up another.
</P>
<P>
   Leeds fielded Bowyer even though he was due to appear in court
on Friday, accused of involvement in a racial attack on a
19-year-old Asian student in downtown Leeds in January. Another
Leeds star, Jonathan Woodgate, is scheduled to appear, as well, but
he was missing from Thursday's game because of an injury.
</P>
<P>
   Bowyer beat two Slavia players before setting up a goal for
Jason Wilcox six minutes before halftime. Harry Kewell scored in
the 54th and Bowyer connected six minutes later off a pass from
Michael Bridges.
</P>
<P>
   The wins highlighted English soccer's return as a European
soccer power. Defending champion Manchester United and Chelsea
already have clinched quarterfinal berths in the Champions Cup.
</P>
<P>
   Turkey's Galatasaray won 4-1 at Mallorca and Celta de Vigo,
which ousted Juventus of Turin in the previous round, played a
scoreless tie at home against Lens.
</P>
<P>
   Galatasaray, coming off a victory over Borussia Dortmund, got
goals from Erdem Arif (45th minute), Belozoglu Emre (48th), Unsal
Hakan (58th) and Buruk Okan (64th). Bisan Lauren scored with 10
minutes left for Celta.
</P>
<P>
   The second legs of the home-and-home, total-goals series are
next week.
</P>
</TEXT>
