<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-16 22:37 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mayors From Five Continents Gather  </HEADLINE>
By MARILYN AUGUST, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   PARIS (AP) -- More than 30 mayors from five continents on
Thursday considered ways to make city life safer, cleaner and more
pleasant as the divide between rich and poor widens.
</P>
<P>
   The two-day Summit of World Mayors, which opened Thursday, was
''an open dialogue'' among urban leaders working in an increasingly
globalized world, said the host, Paris Mayor Jean Tiberi, in an
opening address.
</P>
<P>
   The summit features committees of mayors and international
specialists presenting programs geared to improve the quality of
urban life.
</P>
<P>
   Mayors Anthony A. Williams of Washington D.C. and Willie Brown
of San Francisco were among the 33 mayors at the summit.
</P>
<P>
   ''Being a mayor is all about picking up trash, cleaning the
streets, keeping them lighted and safe,'' Williams told The
Associated Press.
</P>
<P>
   Williams said the goal in the U.S. capital -- celebrating its 200
birthday this year -- is to give all elementary school children
Internet access and provide high schoolers subsidies for college.
</P>
<P>
   Rio de Janeiro's mayor, architect Luis Paulo Conde, showed
slides documenting efforts to clean up Rio's notorious slums.
</P>
<P>
   Warsaw Mayor Pawel Piskorski outlined attempts to improve aging
public services while preserving the historical identity of a city
nearly completely destroyed during World War II.
</P>
<P>
   ''Many more people are driving cars, but the roads can't handle
them,'' he said. ''Warsaw is a mirror that reflects the advantages
and disadvantages of rapid economic growth.''
</P>
<P>
   During the summit, Tiberi and Berlin Mayor Eberhard Diepgen will
inaugurate a new public square, la Place de Berlin, behind the
Champs-Elysees.
</P>
<P>
   The international attention coincides with a crisis at Paris
City hall.
</P>
<P>
   On Wednesday, Tiberi's conservative Rally for the Republic party
suspended him from the leadership of its local branch on suspicions
that he padded the party's Paris membership rolls. Tiberi He vowed
to prove the charges false.
</P>
</TEXT>
