<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bucks 106, Rockets 96  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Ray Allen scored 28 points and Sam Cassell
added 22 as the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Houston Rockets 106-96
Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   Glenn Robinson added 19 as the Bucks handed the Rockets their
fifth straight loss.
</P>
<P>
   Rookie Steve Francis, who matched his season high with 32 points
against New York on Tuesday, had 22 for the Rockets. Kelvin Cato
added 20 and Walt Williams had 19.
</P>
<P>
   Robinson, held to five points in the first half, had 14 after
the break, including eight in the fourth period as the Bucks never
let the lead they grabbed in the third quarter slip away.
</P>
<P>
   The only scare came when Francis hit a 3-pointer that pulled
Houston to 93-87 with 3:29 left. But Robinson answered with a
13-foot jumper and the Bucks never let the margin fall below eight
points the rest of the way.
</P>
<P>
   Houston held a 48-40 halftime lead and protected it until the
Bucks used a 14-5 run to close out the third quarter for a 71-68
lead. Allen helped chip away at the Rockets' lead with nine points
during the quarter before Cassell capped the surge with a free
throw and a jumper.
Notes: Francis picked up a technical for firing his mouth guard
into the crowd after being called for an offensive foul with 45.6
seconds left in the second. ... Bucks guard Vinny Del Negro missed
his second consecutive game with a stress reaction in his right
leg. ... The Bucks' Darvin Ham got a technical for his bad-boy
posturing after second-quarter dunk. ... Allen has scored in double
figures in every game this season. ... With 2:44 left in the third,
the shot clock froze at 21 seconds. After a quick conference, the
referees subtracted seven seconds.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
